> **Template — delete this note after copying.** Copy this file to `skills/[skill-name]/SKILL.md`
> (one directory per skill, named exactly like the frontmatter `name`).
> `name` must match `^[a-z0-9-]+$`, be <=64 chars, and must NOT contain "claude" or "anthropic"
> (those words are fine in prose and in `description`, just not in `name`).
> A skill packages domain knowledge / a named capability as an auto-triggerable instruction set.
> Worked examples: `skills/isomorphic-operations/SKILL.md`, `skills/sjc-indexer/SKILL.md`.
> Bundle helper scripts under `skills/[skill-name]/scripts/` and reference docs under
> `skills/[skill-name]/references/` — they load lazily (progressive disclosure), so keep this
> body under ~5k tokens and push depth into the referenced files.

